e rhythms, envisioned a world in which urban inhabitants have the absolute right to remake the city according to their needs, outside the demands of capital.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aCity and town life in motion pictures. 0aCity planningzNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistoryy20th century. 0aCity symphonies (Motion pictures)zUnited StatesxHistory and criticism. 0aIndependent filmszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aRhythm in motion pictures 0aRhythm in motion pictures. 0aUrban renewalzNew York (State)zNew YorkxHistoryy20th century. 0aUtopias in motion pictures. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Film Studies. 4aFilm, Visual Culture, and Performing Arts : Mass Media. 4aHistory : Social and Cultural History. 4aNew York/Regional : New York/Regional. 4aSociology : Urban Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2021z978311149169140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848664240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438486642423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438486642/original  a978-3-11-149169-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles